=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_NamedControl_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 338 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 338.3071
  harmonic_decay_rate: -14.8708
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5010
  pitch_clarity: 59.4937
  inharmonicity: 0.0071
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -6.6583
  resonance_freq: 344.5312

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: NamedControl Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/NamedControl.html
// Tags: NamedControl, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// use NamedControl to create a number of multichannel controls:

a = { SinOsc.ar(NamedControl.kr(\freq, [300, 330, 370], [1, 0.3, 0.02])).sum * 0.1 }.play;
a.setn(\freq, [700, 705, 890]);
a.setn(\freq, [0, 2, 5].midiratio * 400);

// synonymous:
a = { SinOsc.ar(\freq.kr([300, 330, 370], [1, 0.3, 0.02])).sum * 0.1 }.play;
